WEBVTT

00:13.480 --> 00:14.600
All right?

00:15.400 --> 00:17.240
Yeah. You?

00:17.320 --> 00:18.160
Yeah.

00:19.560 --> 00:21.040
Do you want some toa-- Oh.

00:21.840 --> 00:23.040
-So?
-[Tony] What?

00:23.960 --> 00:25.440
Ask me about the date!

00:25.520 --> 00:27.280
Oh, right. Good?

00:28.240 --> 00:31.960
-Yeah. He's, uh... He's funny, isn't he?
-Definitely.

00:33.200 --> 00:34.880
Sort of... rough and...

00:35.640 --> 00:36.480
rugged?

00:36.800 --> 00:38.720
[sighs] Like he lives under a bridge.

00:39.280 --> 00:40.480
[doorbell rings]

00:46.400 --> 00:47.960
-All right?
-[Tony] Yeah.

00:48.040 --> 00:49.160
Is Roxy in there?

00:49.640 --> 00:52.440
-Yeah, why?
-Well, I've just popped round to see her.

00:52.840 --> 00:55.040
Surely you've popped round
to deliver my mail?

00:55.480 --> 00:57.320
You haven't got any mail.
Can I come in, then?

00:57.400 --> 00:58.400
It's like a zombie movie.

00:58.480 --> 01:00.680
You're always just outside the house
trying to get in.

01:00.760 --> 01:02.120
[Pat] Don't be antisocial.

01:11.680 --> 01:14.080
-Can I have that last bit of toast?
-Yeah.

01:14.280 --> 01:15.560
Ah. Cheers, babe.

01:15.640 --> 01:17.760
-Do you want something on it?
-No, you're all right.

01:17.840 --> 01:19.720
-Got any peanut butter?
-No.

01:19.800 --> 01:22.440
-Don't worry about it, honestly.
-Sure? I'll pop out and...

01:22.960 --> 01:24.560
-Honestly, don't worry.
-All right, good.

01:24.640 --> 01:25.640
[doorbell rings]

01:26.560 --> 01:30.160
Oh! I didn't tell you, did I?
Sue Fyers at work got fired.

01:30.240 --> 01:31.240
[Roxy] What for?

01:31.320 --> 01:32.320
Flashing.

01:33.200 --> 01:34.440
-Front or back?
-[door closes]

01:34.520 --> 01:36.640
Dunno, but the union's involved.
I'm staying out of it.

01:36.720 --> 01:40.040
-Right, I've got to go.
-All right. See you later, mate.

01:40.120 --> 01:41.280
Get out!

01:41.840 --> 01:43.840
-Eh?
-[Tony] What is it?

01:43.920 --> 01:46.400
A woman suing a doctor
for a botched surgery.

01:46.480 --> 01:49.000
-[Tony] Right.
-Someone blows hot and cold, don't they?

01:49.480 --> 01:51.840
Could've done with an egg,
but forget about it.

01:52.560 --> 01:54.640
What happened to you last night?
You bailed early.

01:54.720 --> 01:56.480
Yeah, sorry. Um...

01:56.800 --> 01:58.080
What time did you get home?

01:58.640 --> 02:00.000
Uh... About ten.

02:00.080 --> 02:01.080
I got in at four.

02:01.680 --> 02:03.000
Completely smashed.

02:03.560 --> 02:05.480
Covered in kebab and fanny juice.

02:06.240 --> 02:07.200
Don't ask me how.

02:07.760 --> 02:08.720
I wasn't gonna.

02:08.800 --> 02:11.560
Did too much chang,
so I was lying in bed doing the luge...

02:11.640 --> 02:15.000
till the alarm went off,
then, boom, shower! Coffee.

02:15.080 --> 02:17.880
Suit straight down the dry cleaners. Work.

02:20.440 --> 02:22.200
I got home and I cried a little bit.

02:22.600 --> 02:24.960
Dry cleaners are used to it.
I've shat myself twice.

02:26.280 --> 02:28.120
[clicks tongue] Right. Um...

02:28.840 --> 02:31.480
-Just, sorry, to go back to... me.
-[therapist sighs]

02:32.320 --> 02:33.320
I, um...

02:33.960 --> 02:37.200
I think that I was crying
because I don't want to give up on her,

02:37.280 --> 02:41.880
you know, I don't want to give up on us.
And... all I want to do is

02:41.960 --> 02:44.320
just... talk to her and beg her

02:44.400 --> 02:46.320
to let us go back to how it was.

02:46.400 --> 02:48.880
-Matt--
-But I don't want to stifle her. I don't--

02:48.960 --> 02:50.760
-Women don't want this.
-Yeah.

02:50.840 --> 02:52.600
OK? It's pathetic.

02:53.560 --> 02:54.440
Begging.

02:55.040 --> 02:57.400
[scoffs] How is that good for a family?

02:59.560 --> 03:03.200
Females choose mates
based on their strength.

03:03.760 --> 03:05.480
OK? On their power.

03:06.680 --> 03:08.400
Their capabilities to provide...

03:09.200 --> 03:10.360
and keep them safe.

03:12.240 --> 03:14.680
We're descended
from fucking cavemen, Matt.

03:16.040 --> 03:18.160
We go out,
we kill a saber-toothed tiger,

03:18.240 --> 03:19.600
we bring it back, we share it out,

03:19.680 --> 03:22.200
and then we give the fittest bird
a good fucking seeing to.

03:23.200 --> 03:24.480
That's where we're from.

03:26.240 --> 03:29.120
Yeah, I just don't think
that's really... me.

03:29.200 --> 03:30.240
No, it's not.

03:32.080 --> 03:33.160
Being you

03:33.240 --> 03:36.120
will not win her back.
It's as simple as that.

03:36.200 --> 03:38.200
-You've tried that, didn't work.
-Yeah. No.

03:38.280 --> 03:39.640
She thinks you're a loser.

03:39.720 --> 03:40.560
Solution?

03:42.400 --> 03:44.520
Be something fucking better!

03:44.600 --> 03:46.280
Be something fucking stronger.

03:46.680 --> 03:47.640
-Yeah?
-Mm.

03:47.720 --> 03:48.640
Lie.

03:49.200 --> 03:50.040
Cheat.

03:50.840 --> 03:51.920
Just be a man.

03:54.440 --> 03:55.440
But not you.

03:56.360 --> 03:58.840
When did you start...
having all this done?

03:59.720 --> 04:01.200
[woman] 'Bout five years ago.

04:01.840 --> 04:04.360
Started on, like, botox...

04:04.440 --> 04:07.360
and, like, filler for wrinkles an' that.

04:08.600 --> 04:09.840
[Tony] How old were you?

04:10.240 --> 04:11.480
Early 20s.

04:12.680 --> 04:14.120
What wrinkles did you have?

04:14.200 --> 04:15.200
[woman groans]

04:15.280 --> 04:17.840
Dunno, like, frown lines an' that.

04:19.800 --> 04:22.040
-Right.
-[woman] Yeah, then I proper got into it.

04:22.120 --> 04:23.520
I just couldn't get enough.

04:24.000 --> 04:25.600
And then I got my lips done,

04:25.680 --> 04:27.560
and I had a bit of a reaction.

04:27.640 --> 04:29.640
But that settled down in the end.

04:29.720 --> 04:32.360
And then I wanted to go bigger,
then this happened.

04:33.200 --> 04:36.480
My whole face was paralyzed.
It's only just gone back to normal.

04:37.120 --> 04:38.880
-Has it?
-Yeah.

04:38.960 --> 04:40.080
My boobs leak.

04:41.480 --> 04:42.720
They're fake an' all.

04:43.160 --> 04:44.480
-Are they?
-[woman] Yeah.

04:44.560 --> 04:46.240
-I mean, rock hard.
-[dull tapping]

04:46.680 --> 04:48.320
-Right.
-[woman sighs]

04:48.800 --> 04:49.640
Yeah.

04:50.080 --> 04:53.760
Sorry, and that was the same guy...
that did your face?

04:53.840 --> 04:56.000
Yeah. I was furious.

04:56.080 --> 04:58.040
-Still am.
-[Tony] Are you?

04:58.880 --> 04:59.880
It's hard to tell.

04:59.960 --> 05:02.240
[woman] If you think
he botched my face and chest,

05:02.320 --> 05:03.680
you should see my minge.

05:04.840 --> 05:06.320
It's like a butcher's bin.

05:08.640 --> 05:09.560
Sorry,

05:10.000 --> 05:12.040
you went back to him to have your...

05:12.480 --> 05:14.520
-Minge.
-Yeah, I know. I didn't want to say the...

05:14.600 --> 05:18.080
Yeah, he did it for half price, though.
'Cause of how he'd ruined my face.

05:18.160 --> 05:19.000
[Tony] Right.

05:20.560 --> 05:22.480
Why would you want to have that done?

05:26.480 --> 05:27.840
I think I've got a problem.

05:29.360 --> 05:30.240
Yeah.

05:30.760 --> 05:31.880
I mean, it might be...

05:32.800 --> 05:34.000
like an addiction.

05:35.000 --> 05:38.560
-What, do you mean, like, I can't help it?
-[Tony] Well, I guess so,

05:38.640 --> 05:42.160
but... I mean, if you acknowledge it,
there's a chance you can...

05:42.800 --> 05:44.480
get... you know, get help.

05:44.560 --> 05:46.760
-Do you think I'm mental?
-Well... [sighs]

05:47.080 --> 05:48.400
No more than the rest of us.

05:49.720 --> 05:52.800
As I say, we're all screwed up
in one way or another.

05:52.880 --> 05:54.360
It sort of makes you normal.

05:55.000 --> 05:56.000
[strangled wail]

05:56.080 --> 05:57.240
[chuckles wryly]

05:57.320 --> 05:58.720
-Are you laughing?
-No.

05:58.800 --> 05:59.720
[Tony] Crying?

06:00.120 --> 06:01.000
-Oh.
-[Tony] Oh...

06:01.080 --> 06:01.920
Um...

06:02.480 --> 06:04.280
No, they've fucked my tear ducts.

06:06.400 --> 06:08.480
-[sighs] Take a picture.
-Yeah.

06:08.880 --> 06:10.080
[woman sniffs, clears throat]

06:11.440 --> 06:12.400
[camera clicks]

06:12.480 --> 06:14.400
-[woman] Got it?
-[Lenny] Yeah. Great.

06:19.240 --> 06:20.480
-Hiya.
-[Matt] Hey.

06:22.600 --> 06:24.880
Are you going
to that am-dram cabaret thing?

06:26.200 --> 06:27.440
I dunno. Why?

06:28.000 --> 06:30.400
Well... wondered if you'd like
to come with me?

06:31.520 --> 06:33.920
-What do you mean? You mean you're going?
-[Kath] Yeah.

06:34.000 --> 06:36.800
Thought we could have a drink before
and sit together.

06:38.760 --> 06:40.480
Right. I'm not sure if I'm going.

06:40.840 --> 06:43.160
Right. Well, would you like to go...

06:44.080 --> 06:45.040
with me?

06:46.240 --> 06:48.960
Well, with everyone, really.
Everyone's going. We'd all be there.

06:49.040 --> 06:51.280
Yeah, but I'm saying
would you like to sit with me?

06:52.280 --> 06:54.200
But I don't know if I'm going.
And we don't know

06:54.280 --> 06:55.960
-what seats will be free.
-If you don't want

06:56.040 --> 06:57.760
-to go with me, just say.
-No, it's not that.

06:57.840 --> 07:00.520
-I haven't even checked my diary.
-Well, go on, then.

07:00.600 --> 07:02.640
-What?
-Well, check it. It's right there.

07:03.920 --> 07:06.480
Oh, no.
It's hardly on the right page, is it?

07:11.680 --> 07:16.040
-There's nothing in there at the moment.
-Yeah. Right. Well, I'll, uh...

07:17.280 --> 07:18.640
pencil that in, then.

07:19.920 --> 07:22.360
Um, I will have to check my master diary
as well.

07:22.440 --> 07:24.480
-You've got a master diary?
-Yeah.

07:24.560 --> 07:27.160
I've got work here,
and then personal at home,

07:27.240 --> 07:30.800
so I tend to mix and match,
actually, so... Tony?

07:30.880 --> 07:33.000
Can I just... Sorry, Kath, I've got...

07:33.080 --> 07:34.560
Tony, we've got our, um...

07:36.040 --> 07:36.920
meeting.

07:39.560 --> 07:41.040
Um... Shut the door.

07:46.160 --> 07:48.440
Kath just asked me to sit next to her
at the cabaret thing.

07:48.520 --> 07:49.520
Great.

07:49.600 --> 07:51.320
-I need to get out of it.
-Why?

07:51.400 --> 07:53.920
-Please help me get out of it. Please.
-How?

07:54.480 --> 07:56.280
Say you're thinking
of killing yourself again.

07:57.400 --> 07:59.960
Say I'm thinking
of killing myself next Thursday?

08:00.040 --> 08:01.400
Well, I'll tell her, then.

08:01.480 --> 08:05.240
You'll tell her you can't go with her
'cause I'm thinking of killing myself?

08:06.000 --> 08:07.720
I'm not saying
I'm thinking of killing myself

08:07.800 --> 08:10.400
'cause you're too chicken to say
you don't want to go on a date.

08:10.480 --> 08:12.400
[sighs] For fuck's sake,
it's just a favor.

08:12.480 --> 08:14.560
And do you know the fable,
<i>The Boy Who Cried Wolf?</i>

08:14.640 --> 08:16.200
-Yeah.
-Yeah. Right.

08:16.280 --> 08:18.840
So, what happens when
I really am thinking of killing myself,

08:18.920 --> 08:22.360
and everyone goes, "Nah, he's just trying
to get his cowardly brother-in-law

08:22.440 --> 08:23.480
out of a date"?

08:24.200 --> 08:27.160
Well, no, that's different in that case,
isn't it?

08:27.240 --> 08:29.640
'Cause he admitted it.
He was like, "Nah, only joking."

08:29.720 --> 08:31.080
So they all knew he was lying.

08:31.160 --> 08:33.120
And he kept doing it, so it was obvious.

08:33.200 --> 08:35.480
We'll only use this lie once,
and we'll never admit to it.

08:35.560 --> 08:40.160
So, the moral of that fable is:
"Never admit you were lying,

08:40.240 --> 08:41.320
-ever..."
-Yeah.

08:41.400 --> 08:44.920
"...and always use different lies
each time"?

08:45.520 --> 08:46.440
Yeah.

08:46.520 --> 08:47.760
Nice message.

08:47.840 --> 08:48.800
-No.
-Come on.

08:48.880 --> 08:49.720
No.

08:50.040 --> 08:51.720
-Fuck's sake.
-You're on your own.

08:52.920 --> 08:53.960
[door closes]

08:54.040 --> 08:56.040
[sentimental music plays]

09:03.280 --> 09:05.080
[birds chirping]

09:28.760 --> 09:30.040
[Tony] There we go, Dad.

09:33.200 --> 09:34.080
Good.

09:34.160 --> 09:35.400
There. You're all right.

09:36.360 --> 09:38.200
-Hi.
-Hiya.

09:38.280 --> 09:40.120
[Tony's dad breathes out heavily]

09:42.200 --> 09:45.040
Tony, I'm not going to sit around
and wait for you to make a move,

09:45.120 --> 09:46.400
I have to get on with my life.

09:47.680 --> 09:50.080
-Why are you acting weird?
<i>-I'm </i>acting weird?

09:50.160 --> 09:51.560
For fuck's sake, Tony!

09:51.640 --> 09:53.400
I'm just a bit fed up, all right?

09:53.480 --> 09:56.040
-My wife died. My dad--
-Yes, I know.

09:56.120 --> 09:57.600
Oh, sorry if that bores you.

09:57.680 --> 09:59.920
Seriously? Fucking hell.

10:01.120 --> 10:02.200
Was it just a drink?

10:03.080 --> 10:03.920
Fuck's sake.

10:04.000 --> 10:06.040
It's just a question. Was it just a drink?

10:06.120 --> 10:08.360
[exasperated] Yes, it was just a drink!

10:09.040 --> 10:10.680
OK. Good.

10:12.000 --> 10:13.200
[plumps pillow]

10:13.280 --> 10:15.640
But it might not always be
just a drink, though.

10:23.840 --> 10:25.560
Dad, say, "Simon is a cunt."

10:27.200 --> 10:28.040
What?

10:29.480 --> 10:30.720
"Simon is a cunt."

10:32.640 --> 10:33.480
Say it.

10:35.120 --> 10:37.080
-Yeah.
-"Simon is a cunt."

10:38.720 --> 10:39.720
Remember that.

10:42.000 --> 10:42.920
Right.

10:43.360 --> 10:45.360
[wistful instrumental music plays]

10:46.080 --> 10:47.040
[nurse] All right?

10:47.920 --> 10:50.360
-Is it OK? Not too hot?
-[woman] No, it's good.

10:50.440 --> 10:52.280
[nurse] Yeah. Manage another one?

10:53.520 --> 10:56.240
You'll feel so much better
if you eat this. That's it.

10:58.480 --> 11:00.720
-[indistinct chatter]
-[spoon clinking]

11:01.920 --> 11:03.640
That's better, eh? OK?

11:03.720 --> 11:04.880
-Yeah.
-Yeah?

11:07.960 --> 11:08.840
Hi.

11:09.360 --> 11:11.480
-Hi.
-I've brought you a few jumpers.

11:11.560 --> 11:14.680
-It's getting a bit chillier outside.
-Great. Thanks.

11:14.760 --> 11:18.160
[chuckles lightly] I mean, yeah,
can never have too many jumpers.

11:18.240 --> 11:20.560
Um... I was gonna call you, actually.

11:20.640 --> 11:22.160
Um, you know the cabaret thing

11:22.240 --> 11:23.600
-that they're doing?
-Yeah.

11:24.560 --> 11:26.080
I wondered if you wanted to come.

11:26.600 --> 11:28.640
I'd have to sort a babysitter.

11:28.720 --> 11:30.600
No, you can bring George.
It's for everyone.

11:31.200 --> 11:32.880
Oh... I'm not sure.

11:33.520 --> 11:36.320
Yeah. Um...
You'd be doing me a favor, actually.

11:36.800 --> 11:39.000
-Kath's asked me to go with her.
-Why?

11:40.280 --> 11:41.960
I think she's got a thing for me.

11:42.040 --> 11:43.360
Well, tell her you can't

11:43.440 --> 11:45.400
'cause you're going
with your wife and child.

11:46.400 --> 11:47.600
Right. Yeah.

11:49.160 --> 11:51.640
-Uh...
-I mean, it's nice of her, though, really,

11:51.720 --> 11:53.840
'cause she probably thought
you were lonely.

11:53.920 --> 11:55.240
-Probably.
-Yeah.

11:55.320 --> 11:56.840
I was thinking of coming,

11:56.920 --> 11:59.080
I just didn't know
whether George would be allowed.

11:59.160 --> 12:01.120
-He is, yeah.
-That's good, yeah.

12:01.200 --> 12:04.200
-OK, well... I'd better go.
-Yeah.

12:04.280 --> 12:06.960
-Thanks for the...
-Um, but I'll see you later.

12:08.360 --> 12:10.080
[gentle instrumental music plays]

12:12.560 --> 12:14.720
-Hi. You all right? Yeah, good.
-[Jill] You all right?

12:18.280 --> 12:19.280
[Tony] All right?

12:24.000 --> 12:28.080
-Um... Kath, about the, um, cabaret thing.
-Yeah?

12:29.120 --> 12:30.920
I'm gonna go with Jill and George.

12:32.320 --> 12:34.480
Yeah, fine. Brilliant.

12:35.680 --> 12:36.520
[Kath] Great.

12:39.640 --> 12:42.680
-I'm killing myself that night!
-Don't... [sighs heavily]

12:44.840 --> 12:45.680
What?

12:46.760 --> 12:48.800
Oh. Nothing, it was a...

12:48.880 --> 12:49.720
Weird!

12:52.160 --> 12:54.280
[wistful instrumental music plays]

12:57.320 --> 12:58.400
Do you want a coffee?

13:00.520 --> 13:01.360
Why?

13:01.880 --> 13:02.760
Why?

13:04.080 --> 13:05.800
Dunno, 'cause it tastes nice?

13:08.120 --> 13:10.240
Come on,
let's go for a nice coffee, and...

13:10.320 --> 13:13.320
talk about really interesting things
like... advertising.

13:13.880 --> 13:15.440
-Yeah?
-Yeah, all right.

13:18.640 --> 13:19.920
[footsteps recede]

13:28.920 --> 13:30.360
-There you go.
-Thanks.

13:31.800 --> 13:33.240
[Tony sighs tiredly]

13:35.120 --> 13:37.280
Did I embarrass myself with Matt, then?

13:37.360 --> 13:38.360
Definitely not.

13:38.920 --> 13:41.280
Why would you be embarrassed
about being honest

13:41.360 --> 13:43.400
and saying something nice?
He should be flattered.

13:43.480 --> 13:44.720
I think he was scared!

13:45.480 --> 13:47.760
[chuckles sadly]
I'm obviously not his type.

13:48.720 --> 13:50.320
Someone just got there first.

13:50.400 --> 13:52.960
But, um... you didn't do anything wrong.

13:53.040 --> 13:54.360
You showed your feelings.

13:55.040 --> 13:56.040
That's good.

13:56.880 --> 13:58.600
I wish I'd shown my feelings more.

13:59.360 --> 14:01.000
With Lisa. Um...

14:01.640 --> 14:02.480
I...

14:03.720 --> 14:06.680
Sometimes, I'd be embarrassed
to hold hands in public.

14:07.600 --> 14:10.480
Or if we were on the phone
and there was people around,

14:10.880 --> 14:13.160
she'd always say, "Bye. Love you."

14:13.240 --> 14:15.200
And I would go, "Me too."

14:15.280 --> 14:17.200
And she'd laugh, 'cause she'd know.

14:18.040 --> 14:18.880
Yeah.

14:19.440 --> 14:21.120
Sometimes, I was out, working late.

14:21.200 --> 14:23.600
The phone would go, and I'd think,
"Oh, God, what's happened?"

14:23.680 --> 14:26.520
And I'd go, "Hello?"
I'd go, "What's wrong?" And, um...

14:27.800 --> 14:30.160
she'd say,
"Nothing's wrong, I just love you."

14:30.240 --> 14:31.480
[chokes back sobs]

14:35.600 --> 14:38.560
So... And one day,
you'll meet someone, and it'll be...

14:39.240 --> 14:40.480
Life will be brilliant.

14:41.160 --> 14:42.000
So, uh...

14:43.440 --> 14:46.440
Nothing to feel sad about. Not yet.
[strangled giggle]

14:48.920 --> 14:50.920
[mournful instrumental music plays]

14:56.960 --> 14:58.960
I'm going to... walk for...

14:59.800 --> 15:00.800
OK.

15:00.880 --> 15:02.560
-Thanks for the coffee.
-Sure.

15:02.640 --> 15:06.280
Oh, and thanks for telling me that thing
about your wife calling you.

15:06.360 --> 15:07.360
It was lovely.

15:08.360 --> 15:09.960
-See you later.
-See you later.

