20:38.960 --> 20:42.160
...I wouldn't say no
to the company of a nice lady.

20:42.240 --> 20:43.240
[chuckles]

20:45.640 --> 20:46.920
That's all that matters.

20:48.640 --> 20:51.000
I had the best marriage imaginable.

20:52.000 --> 20:52.840
Magical.

20:53.480 --> 20:54.360
Uh...

20:54.880 --> 20:58.040
So, when, um, Lisa, my wife,

20:58.120 --> 20:59.480
when she died,

20:59.560 --> 21:02.080
I was suicidal, and depressed.

21:02.160 --> 21:05.120
And everyone was so nice,
everyone tried to help me and...

21:05.200 --> 21:09.400
they sort of saved me, so...
I wanted to do something nice back.

21:10.000 --> 21:13.840
But, um, anyway, you're a nice guy,
and I just want you to know,

21:14.800 --> 21:16.760
you know, the whole story, and, uh...

21:17.720 --> 21:20.000
I mean, if you weren't to sell it, um,

21:20.080 --> 21:22.880
we could... you know, give it another go.

21:23.280 --> 21:25.720
If it didn't work out,
you could sell it next year.

21:26.160 --> 21:27.400
It might work, and...

21:28.000 --> 21:31.560
